rounds.event: The last known speaker of Akkala Sami dies, rendering the language extinct.
deaths: Bob Monkhouse, English comedian, actor, and game show host

rounds.event: Czech writer, philosopher and dissident Václav Havel is elected the first post-communist President of Czechoslovakia.
births: Harri Säteri, Finnish ice hockey player

rounds.event: Japan renounces the Washington Naval Treaty of 1922 and the London Naval Treaty of 1930.
A magnitude 6.4 earthquake hits near the town of Petrinja in Sisak-Moslavina County, Croatia, killing 7 people.
Turkish Airlines Flight 278 (a Boeing 737-400) crashes on approach to Van Ferit Melen Airport in Van, Turkey, killing 57 of the 76 people on board.
